From 4e057f890360e129a7fad25c520314522665e5b3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Xi Ruoyao <xry111@xry111.site>
Date: Fri, 19 Dec 2025 11:34:11 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] LOONGSON3: AOSCOS: allow dlopen shared objects with
 executable stack for now

Commit 0ca8785a2851 ("elf: Do not change stack permission on
dlopen/dlmopen") has disabled dlopen shared objects requiring executable
stack by default unless the program or one of its dependency (via
DT_NEEDED, either direct or indirect) already requires executable stack.

Unfortunately, on loongson3 GCC had had a bug causing many shared
objects incorrectly announcing the requirement of executable stack.  The
bug was only "recently" fixed at https://gcc.gnu.org/r15-3205.  So if
the program and all of its dependencies are built with Core 13, but the
dlopen'ed shared object is built with Core 12, the dlopen will fail.
This seems causing a massive system breakage on loongson3.

Change the default for now until we rebuild everything with Core 13.

Signed-off-by: Xi Ruoyao <xry111@xry111.site>
---
 elf/dl-tunables.list | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/elf/dl-tunables.list b/elf/dl-tunables.list
index c03c9967f0..c666ffb5db 100644
--- a/elf/dl-tunables.list
+++ b/elf/dl-tunables.list
@@ -139,7 +139,7 @@ glibc {
       type: INT_32
       minval: 0
       maxval: 2
-      default: 1
+      default: 2
     }
   }
 
-- 
2.52.0

